    dc:creator "Karaouzas, Ioannis" ;
    dc:date "2017" ;
    dc:title "The larva of Agapetus episkopi Malicky 1972 (Trichoptera: Glossosomatidae), including a key to the larvae of Glossosomatidae of the Hellenic western Balkan region" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1001152>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1001154>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1001160>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1001156> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1001152>
    dc:description "FIGURES 1 – 6. Agapetus episkopi Malicky 1972, final instar larva. 1, head, dorsal; 2, head, dorsolateral; 3, head, ventral (b = anterior branch of ventral ecdysial line, el = ventral ecdysial line, sc = submental sclerite); 3 A, unworn left mandible, ventral; 3 B, strongly worn right mandible, ventral; 4, thorax, dorsal (p = pronotal sclerite, s = mesonotal sclerite, t = metanotal sclerite); 5, left foreleg, posterior face; 6, left midleg, posterior face. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (except Figs. 3 A, 3 B: 0.1 mm)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1001152/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1001154>
    dc:description "FIGURES 7 – 13. Agapetus episkopi Malicky 1972, final instar larva. 7, left hind leg, posterior face; 8, thorax, ventral (ms = mesosternal sclerite, ps = prosternal sclerite); 9, metathorax and abdominal segments I – IV, right ventrolateral (ls = lateral seta, vs = ventral seta); 10, abdominal segments IV – IX, right lateral (vs = ventral seta); 11, posterior tip of abdomen, right posterolateral (ap = anal papillae). 12, posterior tip of abdomen, dorsal (arrow = left posterolateral seta on tergite IX; ss = alveolae of tiny pair of pale setae); 13, larval case, ventral. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1001154/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1001160>
    dc:description "FIGURE 20. Glossosomatidae genn. spp., final instar larvae. 20, Synagapetus iridipennis McLachlan 1879, larval case, ventral (arrows = collar of sand grains). 21, Agapetus laniger Pictet 1834, head, frontal (a = pale central patch on frontoclypeus, b = pale patches on posterior sections of parietalia). Scale bars: 0.5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1001160/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1001156>
    dc:description "FIGURES 14 – 19. Glossosomatidae genn. spp., final instar larvae. 14 – 15, Agapetus episkopi Malicky 1972: 14, larval case, dorsal; 15, larval case, lateral. 16 – 17. Glossosoma conforme Neboiss 1963: 16, thorax, dorsal (p = pronotum); 17, posterior tip of abdomen, right lateral (arrow = left lateral seta on abdominal tergite IX). 18, Glossosoma bifidum McLachlan 1879, posterior tip of abdomen, right lateral (arrow = left lateral seta on abdominal tergite IX). 19, Synagapetus iridipennis McLachlan 1879, abdominal segments I – IV, right lateral (ls = lateral seta). Scale bars: 0.5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1001156/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

